        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The graphics used in this service procedure are for 5000i and 9000i Models and may appear
                        slightly different for models built before July, 1999; however the procedure Steps are the same
                        for 5000 and 9000 Models built between July, 1996 and July, 1999.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Based on experience, 75% of the trucks with hood noise can be corrected by replacing the
                        center hood guide only.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0109011" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0109011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="472px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Component Locations</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CENTER HOOD GUIDE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HOOD GUIDE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HOOD BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0109011">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                for component location.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the existing center hood guide (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0109011">Figure 1, Item 1</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0109012">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0109012" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0109012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="368px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Center Hood Guide</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new center hood guide. Tighten the two hex head screws to 20 to 22 Lbf-Ft
                    (27 to 30 NM).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Perform a noise evaluation on the vehicle with the new center hood guide installed by
                    driving the vehicle on a rough roadway. If the noise issue has been corrected, the service procedure
                    is completed. If noise is still present, continue to the next Step.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two (passenger and driver side) rear hood guides (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0109011">Figure 1, Item 2</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0109013">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0109013" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0109013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3. Hood Rear Support Guide</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new rear hood guide on the passenger and driver side. Tighten the two hex head
                    screws to 20 to 22 Lbf-Ft (27 to 30 NM).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two (passenger and driver side) hood brackets (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0109011">Figure 1, Item 3</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0109014">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0109014" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0109014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4. Hood Bracket</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new hood bracket on the passenger and driver side. Tighten the screws so that
                    slight hood bracket movement is allowed and hood adjustment is possible. Close the hood.
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If the hood does not close completely, re-open the hood and adjust the hood brackets
                        until the hood completely closes. When the hood is properly adjusted the hood latches can be
                        engaged.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">When the hood adjustment is completed, open the hood and tighten the new hood
                        bracket hex head screws to 20 to 22 Lbf-Ft (27 to 30 NM). The service procedure is completed.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Troubleshooting</title>
            <specpara>
                <para>Completing the service procedure should eliminate the hood noise issue, however, if some hood
                    noise is still observed, the following Steps should be reviewed.
                </para>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open the hood, loosen and re-adjust either the center hood guide (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0109012">Figure 2</hotlnk>) and/or the hood brackets (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0109014">Figure 4</hotlnk>). The parts may be off center and may require slight
                    adjustment.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the hood rear supports, center hood guide and hood bracket mounting screws are
                    fully engaged and seated to each mounting bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the hood latches are engaged.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
